stylometry: The data mining method we used in class was the clustering model.  This model consisted of gathering a bunch of information and clustering the data to see what data was the best.  For example I used basketball statistics for players and the object of my model was to seek out what players from the index stood out the most and were the best amoung the given statistics.  In order to find these solutions the players were placed in a pool and you had to use the vlookup formula to find out which players were the most valuable.  You also had to find the standard deviation of the data then you used to MATCH formula to to group the data.  After those steps you used the sumxmy2 function to find efficiency of players and then you find the minimum of all the data.  In conclusion, after putting all the data into formula form, I was able to find the top 4 players that were the best in the measured statistics out of the whole field.
